<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233367>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Hyperoche medusarum (Kröyer, 1838). A, G 1, G 2, P 3 – 7 & Us; male (7.7 mm) ZMUC CRU- 20286; Davis St. [61 ° 11 ’ N 49 ° 38.5 ’ W], Godthaab stn. 185, 50 mw, 9 Oct. 1928. B (P 3) & C (P 4), from male (7.8 mm), ZMUC CRU- 20287; E. of Greenland [65 ° 31 ’ N 26 ° 42 ’ W], Dana stn. 4637, 65 mw, 8 Aug. 1933. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (remainder)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233367/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233373>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Hyperoche luetkenides Walker, 1906. A (G 2), B (A 1, A 2) from female (12.8 mm), SAMA C 7936; Prydz Bay, Antarctica [67 ° 28.8 ’ S 68 ° 49.8 ’ E – 67 ° 31.02 ’ S 61 ° 89 ’ E], Aurora Australis stn. 37 C, 164 – 159 m, 12 Feb. 1991. C (G 1, G 2) from ovigerous female (13.5 mm), SAMA C 7937; Prydz Bay, Antarctica [67 ° 53.9 ’ S 71 ° 04.1 ’ E – 67 ° 55.52 ’ S 71 ° 06.5 ’ E], Aurora Australis stn. 28 A, 211 – 249 m, 7 Feb. 1991. Mouthparts from female as per Fig. 8. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (mouthparts); 0.5 mm (remainder)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233373/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

